V<div dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;" trbidi="on">\u000a<div style="background-color: white; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;">\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;">\u000a<b><span style="color: #c00000; font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 18pt; text-transform: uppercase;">NIGHT\u2019S END</span></b></div>\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;">\u000a<b><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 12pt; text-transform: uppercase;">AT BHARATRANG MAHOTSAV 2014</span></b></div>\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;">\u000a<br /></div>\u000a</div>\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="background-color: white; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;">\u000a<b><span style="color: #c00000; font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 14pt;"><span class="aBn" data-term="goog_724659185" style="border-bottom-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-bottom-style: dashed; border-bottom-width: 1px; position: relative; top: -2px; z-index: 0;" tabindex="0"><span class="aQJ" style="position: relative; top: 2px; z-index: -1;">14 Jan 2014, 5.30pm</span></span>, LTG Theatre, New Delhi</span></b></div>\u000a<div style="background-color: white; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;">\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;">\u000a<br /></div>\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;">\u000a<span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 14pt;">An original play about the tiger, forest and human survival</span></div>\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;">\u000a<br /></div>\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;">\u000a<b><span style="color: #c00000; font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 12pt;">Play, Direction:</span></b><b><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;Gowri Ramnarayan</span></b></div>\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;">\u000a<b><span style="color: #c00000; font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 12pt;">Featuring:</span></b><b><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;Sheejith Krishna, Akhila Ramnarayan</span></b></div>\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;">\u000a<b><span style="color: #c00000; font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 12pt;">Produced by:</span></b><b><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;JustUs Repertory, Chennai</span></b></div>\u000a<div style="text-align: center;">\u000a<span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;"><b>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</b></span></div>\u000a<div style="text-align: center;">\u000a<b style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">Tickets:</b><span style="color: #990000; font-family: verdana, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><b>Rs.200/ Rs.100/ Rs. 50/</b></span></span></div>\u000a<div style="text-align: center;">\u000a<span style="color: #990000;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 10pt;"><b><br /></b></span></span></div>\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 0.5in; text-align: center;">\u000a<span style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 10pt;"><b><span style="color: #69645c;">Booking starts on&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #990000;">9th at NSD campus</span><span style="color: #69645c;">&nbsp;for plays from&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #990000;">11th Jan-15th Jan 2013. (</span><span style="color: black;">NIGHT'S END</span><span style="color: #990000;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: black;">on&nbsp;<span class="aBn" data-term="goog_724659186" style="border-bottom-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-bottom-style: dashed; border-bottom-width: 1px; position: relative; top: -2px; z-index: 0;" tabindex="0"><span class="aQJ" style="position: relative; top: 2px; z-index: -1;">14th Jan</span></span></span><span style="color: #990000;">)</span></b></span><br />\u000a<b><span style="color: #69645c; font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 10pt;">A small percentage of tickets available at&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 10pt;"><span style="color: #990000;"><a href="http://in.bookmyshow.com/festival/bharat-rang-mahotsav-tickets/?&amp;utm_source=hm_flb_fest_BRM_040113" style="color: #1155cc;" target="_blank">www.bookmyshow.com</a>,</span></span><span style="color: #69645c; font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;and</span></b></div>\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 0.5in; text-align: center;">\u000a<b><span style="color: #69645c; font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 10pt;">overphone:&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 10pt;"><span style="color: #990000;">Bookmyshow - +91-11-39895050</span></span></b><b style="color: #69645c; font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 10pt; text-align: center;">&nbsp;</b><br />\u000a<b style="color: #69645c; font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 10pt; text-align: center;">(Online booking closes at&nbsp;<span class="aBn" data-term="goog_724659187" style="border-bottom-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-bottom-style: dashed; border-bottom-width: 1px; position: relative; top: -2px; z-index: 0;" tabindex="0"><span class="aQJ" style="position: relative; top: 2px; z-index: -1;">midnight</span></span>&nbsp;before day</b><b style="color: #69645c; font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 10pt; text-align: center;">&nbsp;of the show).</b></div>\u000a<div>\u000a<b style="color: #69645c; font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 10pt; text-align: center;"><br /></b></div>\u000a<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">\u000a<a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-Xp5L1vQPt1o/Usja0hSrsiI/AAAAAAAAEHs/yQCxX9I1lls/s1600/NIGHT%27S+END+PHOTO.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-Xp5L1vQPt1o/Usja0hSrsiI/AAAAAAAAEHs/yQCxX9I1lls/s320/NIGHT'S+END+PHOTO.jpg" height="240" width="320" /></a></div>\u000a<div>\u000a<b style="color: #69645c; font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 10pt; text-align: center;"><br /></b></div>\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;">\u000a<br /></div>\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;">\u000a<b><span style="color: #c00000; font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 12pt;">REVIEWS</span></b><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></div>\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;">\u000a<span style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">A fascinating tale of love, betrayal and loss\u2014an exceptional story of a man\u2019s search for redemption through his valiant attempt to save the tiger and the fragile ecosystem of the forest in which he has chosen to live. All through the taut drama and conflicts you can almost hear the big cat roar\u2026 The eternal human craving to bond with nature\u2026 rarely dealt with such passion on the stage</span></span></div>\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;">\u000a<span style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;"><b><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></b><b><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 18px;">Prithvijit Mitra,&nbsp;<i>The Times of India</i>, 18 November 2013</span></b></span><br />\u000a</div>\u000a</div>\u000a<div style="background-color: white; color: #222222; font-size: 13px; text-align: center;">\u000a<span style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;"><span style="font-size: 11pt;">JustUs, one of India\u2019s few companies committed to providing a different stage experience, brought&nbsp;<i>Night\u2019s End</i>, by Gowri Ramnarayan... (the play) proved yet again how Ramnarayan specializes in exploring important subjects that dramatists rarely take up.&nbsp;</span></span></div>\u000a<div style="background-color: white; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;">\u000a<blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="border-left-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-left-style: solid; border-left-width: 1px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0.8ex; padding-left: 1ex;">\u000a<div style="text-align: left;">\u000a<span style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;"><b>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Ananda Lal,<i>&nbsp;The Telegraph,</i>&nbsp;30 November 2013</b></span></div>\u000a</blockquote>\u000a<br />\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;">\u000a<span style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 18px;">An Indian English play of international class, plunging us into speculation: what will emerge at the end of a long night remote-controlled by powerful interest groups riding roughshod over the powerless?</span></span></div>\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;">\u000a<span style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;"><b><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 18px;">Seetha Ravi,&nbsp;<i>Kalki magazine,</i>&nbsp;30 December 2012</span></b></span></div>\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;">\u000a<span style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;"><br /></span></div>\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;">\u000a<span style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 18px;">Location, imagination, technique were completely new. Inventiveness was visible in sets, backscore and direction. Powerful enactment made the spectator experience the full sweep of emotions.</span></span></div>\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;">\u000a<span style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;"><b><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 18px;">Charukesi,&nbsp;<i>Dinamani,</i>&nbsp;(Indian Express Group), Dec 2012</span></b></span></div>\u000a<div class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;">\u000a<br /></div>\u000a</div>\u000a</div>\u000a
